From 41805f7eb50f31e16839bb302df1bb5c6f30cb50 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mitchell Pleune <mitchpleune@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 23 Aug 2024 09:58:56 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 1/1] Remove deprecared avcodec_close()
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

From [docs](https://ffmpeg.org/doxygen/trunk/deprecated.html) see that
this function call is not needed:

"Do not use this function. Use avcodec_free_context() to destroy a codec
context (either open or closed). Opening and closing a codec context
multiple times is not supported anymore – use multiple codec contexts instead."

avcodec_free_context is already called.

Upstream-Status: Backport [https://github.com/ros-drivers/usb_cam/commit/41805f7eb50f31e16839bb302df1bb5c6f30cb50]
---
 include/usb_cam/formats/mjpeg.hpp | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/include/usb_cam/formats/mjpeg.hpp b/include/usb_cam/formats/mjpeg.hpp
index 2b40bb2..b8d87f7 100644
--- a/include/usb_cam/formats/mjpeg.hpp
+++ b/include/usb_cam/formats/mjpeg.hpp
@@ -164,7 +164,6 @@ public:
       free(m_avoptions);
     }
     if (m_avcodec_context) {
-      avcodec_close(m_avcodec_context);
       avcodec_free_context(&m_avcodec_context);
     }
     if (m_avframe_device) {
-- 
